snippet.textDisplay:
I use extension dreadlocks in a ton of different colors [because I love the color pop, always get tons of compliments] I fit around 70 in my hair, usually wear them for 2 months [yes I do wash my hair but I use shampoo from the Bio shop] and it takes around 8 hours to braid them in without breaks so around 10 with breaks. Takes 4 to 5 hours to take them out. I've been doing this for the past year and 4 months as I am trying to grow my hair for donation. I do get a little haircut every 10 months and my hair is also sooo much healthier, and thicker. I do have a lot of hair to comb out after, simply because there is no natural hair falling out, it's all stuck in the dreads. Also, my hair is growing a lot faster now than before.
I'd definitely say give them a try, Brad. They come in so many colors and shapes, single ended, double ended, have fun with it. Even if just for a few days! Also good to hear your opinion on wearing them, the before and the after taking them out!
snippet.textOriginal:

Takes 4 to 5 hours to take them out. I've been doing this for the past year and 4 months as I am trying to grow my hair for donation. I do get a little haircut every 10 months and my hair is also sooo much healthier, and thicker. I do have a lot of hair to comb out after, simply because there is no natural hair falling out, it's all stuck in the dreads. Also, my hair is growing a lot faster now than before. 
I'd definitely say give them a try, Brad. They come in so many colors and shapes, single ended, double ended, have fun with it. Even if just for a few days! Also good to hear your opinion on wearing them, the before and the after taking them out!

snippet.textDisplay: i didnt take mine down just cut it straight out, people think locks are easy to take care of but they arent really and i had mine for years. im going to be honest dreads/ locks in straight hair looks horrid most times because it either takes very long to lock in place or they dont take care of it i know people with straight hair who thought their locks will look like mine but were disappointed that it didnt i had to explain thaat my hair is kinky and at least for me my hair really likes locking so i had way easier of a time with mine and it was still lots of work to keep my roots from joining and making it one big jank as we call people with one or two very large locks.so people especially people with less kinky hair if you are thinking about putting in locks/ dreads take care of it and keep it from smelling because they smell if they arent dried properly and especially if you dont have kinky hair you hair will slip out of the lock easy or take longer to form thts the most regular complaint ive heard if you really want it have patience and trim even i had to trim of my ends sometimes to keep it looking neat.
